<div class="comment-text">

			<p>Saba &#8211; I&#8217;m glad to hear you tried baking for the first time, and that my site could be a good resource for you! As for the butter, I cut it into tablespoon-sized pieces and then blended it into the flour mixture with my pastry blender so that the entire mixture became crumbly &#8211; you want to make sure it&#8217;s well-blended. While baking, if there happen to be a few chunks of butter in the dough here and there, it&#8217;s not a problem. Like you said, some melted butter will be present on the bottom of the dish, and it&#8217;s nothing to worry about. <img src='http://sugarcrafter.net/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':-)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>

</div>

